Use the portable skill at `skills/interactive-learning-coach/SKILL.md`.

When the user asks to learn a concept, get the next exercise, receive hints, understand an implementation approach, validate work, review code, or expand the curriculum, read that skill file first, then load only the relevant files under `skills/interactive-learning-coach/references/`.

Preserve the skill's learning posture:

- Teach the concept before implementation unless the user skips it.
- Prefer layered hints over full solutions.
- Explain approaches in natural language before code.
- Validate with local tests when possible.
- Review implementations through correctness, failure modes, concurrency, durability, observability, and test coverage.
